A1. Rhyming name for the penalty box, in hockey ~ SINBIN
A7. Prelude before a featured boxing match ~ UNDERCARD
A10. Stuffed tummies, slangily ~ FOODBABIES
A12. Duolingo or Hooters' mascot, e.g. ~ OWL
A13. Soccer score when no one's scored ~ NILNIL
A15. "Finally made the plane into Paris / Honeymooning down by ___" ("The Ballad of John & Yoko") ~ THESEINE
A17. "The dog ate my homework," among others ~ POOREXCUSES
A20. Sweet frozen treat with a Louie-Bloo Raspberry variety ~ OTTERPOP
A21. Diana's duet partner on "Endless Love" ~ LIONEL
A22. The L in LSAT ~ LAW
A25. Decides what to charge ~ SETSAPRICE
A28. Treated "Onion"-style ~ SATIRIZED
A29. Minimal phone signal ~ ONEBAR

D1. Some ground cover ~ SNOW
D2. Any member of BTS, e.g. ~ IDOL
D3. "___!?!? ___ Ryerson!?!?" ("Groundhog Day" line) ~ NED
D4. "One sec," in a text ~ BRB
D5. First line in some 17-Across ~ ICANEXPLAIN
D6. Company that will not stop until every flavor and B-list celebrity has its own namesake Oreo ~ NABISCO
D7. Sight in "Nope" or "Close Encounters" ~ UFO
D8. Put in an agitated state ~ RILEUP
D9. Villeneuve who's directing the next James Bond film ~ DENIS
D11. Wave in math class? ~ SINE
D14. NYC neighborhood home to the Tenement Museum ~ LES
D15. Biggest Starbucks size ~ TRENTA
D16. Opening words of a toast ~ HERESTO
D17. DC wheeler-dealer ~ POL
D18. "King of Soul" Redding ~ OTIS
D19. Great Plains natives (with a name that sounds like 18-Down) ~ OTOES
D22. Minnelli who received the Giving Us Lifetime Achievement Award on "RuPaul's Drag Race" ~ LIZA
D23. Big name in Chromebooks ~ ACER
D24. Add a hyphen to your name, perhaps ~ WED
D26. TSA timesaver, for short ~ PRE
D27. Tease a little ~ RIB


